h served as the basis for the lawsuit.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/82192/arbitron-sues-saga-for-copyright-infringement/ Arbitron Sues Saga For Copyright Infringement] from Radio Insight (May 28, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''29'''\n|The CRTC gives the CBC the OK to allow FM stations [[CBC Radio 2]] and [[Espace Musique]] to start airing commercials on a 3-year term agreement.<ref>[http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/118845/crtc-oks-ads-on-cbc-radio-2-espace-musique-for-3-y CRTC OKs Ads On CBC Radio 2, Espace Musique For 3-Year Term] from All Access (May 29, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''30'''\n|Results Radio shuffles its two rimshot [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento]] outlets, as [[Placerville, California|Placerville]]-licensed [[KVMX-FM|KCCL]] moves its Classic Hits format to and trades call letters with [[KCCL|KMJE]], who moved into the market from [[Woodland, California]], giving it a better coverage in the area. KMJE then starts stunting until December 1, when it flips to Regional Mexican as \"La Buena 92.1\" under new owner Lotus, who acquired the station in September.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/82214/k-hits-sacramento-moves-to-101-5/ K-Hits Sacramento Moves To 101.5] from Radio Insight (May 30, 2013)</ref>\n|}\n\n===June===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Date\n! Event\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1'''\n|Format changes come to [[Gainesville, Florida]], as JVC Media, citing what they see as under performing stations, flips News/Talk [[WGMW|WBXY]] to Dance<ref>[http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/118990/wbxy-is-dancin-in-gainesville WBXY Is Dancin' In Gainesville] from All Access (June 3, 2013)</ref> (Ironically, the decision would also result in the early termination of morning hosts Jake Fuller and Ward Scott after bad-mouthing the move made by the new owners on-air on May 30) and at the same time transform fellow Sports sister [[WYGC]] to a simulcast of 