dio/1566479/pandora-buys-terrestrial-radio-station-in-south-dakota-aims-for \"Pandora Buys Terrestrial Radio Station in South Dakota, Aims for Lower ASCAP Royalties\"] from Billboard (June 11, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''14'''\n|KNBQ/[[Centralia, Washington]] flips from a simulcast of Sports sister [[KJR (AM)|KJR]]/[[Seattle, Washington|Seattle]] to Adult Top 40 as \"102.9 Now,\" under the [[KZTM|KYNW]] call sign. The station is targeting the [[Olympia, Washington|Olympia]] and [[Tacoma, Washington|Tacoma]] areas.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/83816/clear-channel-launches-102-9-now-seattle/ Clear Channel Launches 102.9 Now Seattle] from Radio Insight (June 14, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=2|'''17'''\n|For the first time since making the transition to AC in 1989 as \"Lite 93.9,\" [[WLIT-FM|WLIT]]/Chicago shifts to Hot AC and rebrands its moniker to \"My 93.9.\"<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/83851/lites-out-in-chicago/ \"Lite\u2019s Out In Chicago\"] from Radio Insight (June 17, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|Sports talk [[WQXI (AM)|WQXI]]/Atlanta fires the hosts of its morning program \"Mayhem In The AM\" (Steak Sharpiro, Nick Cellini, and Chris Dimino) after they used a mock interview of former [[New Orleans Saints]] player [[Steve Gleason]], who is battling [[Lou Gerhig's disease]] by parodying his robotic voice as if they were answering questions to him (as Gleason has lost the ability to speak and has to use a computer device to communicate).<ref>[http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/119452/firings-follow-morning-bit-gone-bad-at-790-the-zon \"Firings Follow Morning Bit Gone Bad At 790 The Zone/Atlanta\"] from All Access (June 17, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''18'''\n|Wasatch Public Media, the owners of [[KCPW-FM|KCPW]]/[[Salt Lake City, Utah|Salt Lake City]], announces that they will drop their affiliation with [[National Public Radio|NPR]] effective June 24 as a way to 