's licensee [[Liberman Broadcasting]]. The new occupant and owner of the 1430 frequency, La Promesa Foundation, launched a Catholic programming format the same day.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/80036/kcoh-houston-to-relocate/ \"KCOH Houston Relocates\"] From Radio Insight (March 1, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|[[WRTH (FM)|WOLT]]/[[Greenville, South Carolina|Greenville]] exits the part-time Dance Top 40/part-time brokered programming format to pick up the Oldies format from AM sister [[WOLI (AM)|WOLI/W289BS]], who in turn takes the brokered programming with Adult Standards filling in most of the other dayparts.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/80914/earth-is-moving-in-greenvillespartanburg/ \"Earth Is Moving In Greenville/Spartanburg\"] from Radio Insight (March 1, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|After 5 months in the format, [[Florence, South Carolina]] Rhythmic oldies trio [[WOLH]]/[[WHYM|WHYM & W255BD]] flipped to [[ESPN Radio]], bringing that Sports Talk network back after former affiliate [[WWFN-FM|WWFN]] switched to [[CBS Sports Radio]] in January.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/81085/espn-radio-returns-to-florence/ \"ESPN Radio Returns To Florence\"] from Radio Insight (March 1, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|The FCC accepts a proposal that would see a signal upgrade for [[WSOS-FM|WSOS]]/[[Jacksonville, Florida|Jacksonville]] from Class C3 to C2. If approved, it would require two Class C stations in [[Savannah, Georgia|Savannah]], [[WQBT]] and [[WIXV]], to switch their signals.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/81092/fcc-report-31-jacksonville-upgrade-could-lead-to-savannah-shuffle/ \"FCC Report 3/1: Jacksonville Upgrade Could Lead To Savannah Shuffle\"] from Radio Insight (March 1, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|Classic rock/classic hits 92.3 Fred FM [[CFRK-FM]] in [[Fredericton, New Brunswick|Fredericton]] abruptly makes its exit as it flips to Top 40/CHR as Hot 92.3\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''3'''\n|[[KMVX|KNOE-FM]]/[[Monroe, Louisiana]] drops Top 