89/miami-reaches-an-evolutionary-state/ \"Miami Reaches An Evolutionary State\"] from Radio Insight (March 12, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''14'''\n|[[Sirius XM Radio]] removes [[Playboy Radio]] from its lineup, with the station continuing as an independent online website.<ref>[http://www.sirius.com/playboyradio Message from Playboy Radio on SiriusXM] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110106084458/http://www.sirius.com/playboyradio |date=2011-01-06 }} (March 14, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=2|'''26'''\n|Smooth Jazz [[WAUN-FM]] and their translators bring the [[Regional Mexican]] format to the [[Green Bay, Wisconsin]] radio market for the first time.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/81310/smooth-bays-shifts-to-regional-mexican/ Smooth Bays Shifts To Regional Mexican] from Radio Insight (March 26, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|[[WKIO|WUIL]]/[[Champaign, Illinois|Champaign]] flips from Active Rock to Classic Hits and brings back the call letters of WKIO, which has heritage in the market from 1978 to 2005 [[WREE|at 92.5]].<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/netgnomes/81272/urock-champaign-urbana-to-rock-no-more/ URock Champaign-Urbana Shifts To Classic Hits] from Radio Insight (March 26, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''28'''\n|Clear Channel flips [[Atlanta]] stations [[WRDA (FM)|WWVA-FM]] and [[WRDG|WWLG]] from Rhythmic Top 40 to Alternative Rock.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/netgnomes/81343/alternative-on-its-way-back-to-atlanta/ Alternative Returns To Atlanta] from Radio Insight (March 28, 2013)</ref>\n|}\n\n===April===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Date\n! Event\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=5|'''1'''\n|The AC format once again goes away in the Minneapolis-St. Paul radio market, as the trimulcast of [[WGVX|WGVX/WRXP/WGVZ]] flips to Sports as \"The Ticket\"; the [[CBS Sports Radio]] affiliate brings the number of Sports outlets in the Twin Cities to three,