le]] begins [[brokered programming|buying airtime]] for a monthly radio show that will air on [[WSYR (AM)|WSYR-AM]]/[[WSYR-FM|FM]].<ref>Naughton, Peter (May 16, 2013). [http://www.cnyradio.com/2013/05/16/former-congresswoman-buerkle-to-host-wsyr-talk-show/ Former Congresswoman Buerkle to host WSYR talk show]. ''CNYRadio.com''. Retrieved May 17, 2013.</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''27'''\n|[[Family Radio]] announces plans to sell off their stations.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/82184/family-radios-stations-on-the-block/ Family Radio Stations On The Block] from Radio Insight (May 27, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''28'''\n|[[Arbitron]] files a lawsuit against Saga Communications for copyright infringement of their ratings service, claiming that Saga, who does not subscribe to Arbitron, allowed management and employees to make decisions on programming and sales rates based on the ratings data it was not contractually licensed to have as well as use it to award employees bonuses. Arbitron cited that this practice was heavily used at Saga's [[Milwaukee, Wisconsin|Milwaukee]] properties [[WJYI]], [[WKLH]], [[WJMR-FM|WJMR]], [[WHQG]] and [[WNRG-FM|WNRG]], which served as the basis for the lawsuit.<ref>[http://radioinsight.com/blog/headlines/82192/arbitron-sues-saga-for-copyright-infringement/ Arbitron Sues Saga For Copyright Infringement] from Radio Insight (May 28, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''29'''\n|The CRTC gives the CBC the OK to allow FM stations [[CBC Radio 2]] and [[Espace Musique]] to start airing commercials on a 3-year term agreement.<ref>[http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/118845/crtc-oks-ads-on-cbc-radio-2-espace-musique-for-3-y CRTC OKs Ads On CBC Radio 2, Espace Musique For 3-Year Term] from All Access (May 29, 2013)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''30'''\n|Results Radio shuffles its two rimshot [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento]] outlets, as [[Placerville, Californi